review:
This game accurately simulates the driving of a tube in London Underground's Circle Line. I will list the PROS, the NEUTRAL and the CONS, based on my experience with the game.

For the PROS, I enlist the following:
- Graphics - for a 2014 game, the graphics are pretty well designed. With a good computer, the whole experience is enhanced because of it;
- Simulation - the fact that you're given pre-service tasks, like turn on your train from cold/dark, up until the strict and challenging timetable, gets you fully immersed on it;
- Environment - the environment on all stations, even though it sounds on a loop, is what you'd expect from a LU's station. With all those "Mind the gap, please" warnings and overall sounds, once again, gets you immersed on the game.

For NEUTRAL factors, I state that the physics are generally good (you have a pretty good inertia simulation - whenever you accelerate or brake the train, depending on how soft or hard you do both), but when you get to some kind of descent or climbing, you don't gain or lose speed, respectively. This is somewhat crucial for a simulation game.

For the CONS, here's the following:
- Bugs - there are some massive bugs on this (dated?) game. Sometimes, when I'm on FPV (first-person view), I get stuck while walking - this is only solvable if I walk in TPV (third-person view);
- DVA/Destination board bug - even if you set those two things up correctly, at the end of the journey you'll get the opposite, on the trip's briefing;
- Random crashes - sometimes, the game gets really laggish and, out of a sudden, it crashes. It happened to me twice.

The fact that all these problems happen is a huge bummer for me, since I was looking forward to play this game for years.
I even tried to run the Windows 10 compatibility tool and checked if all my stuff (GPU, system and other drives) were updated (they are).

Unfortunately, at least for me, the cons overcome the pros, making me wishing for an optimization patch from TML/Aerosoft.

Um excelente simulador de metrô! 

Prós:
- Trens e estações detalhados;
- Sons e anúncios em trens e estações;
- Várias funções. A maioria dos comandos são funcionais;
- Pessoas super realistas;
- Carregamento rápido;
- Fácil de conduzir o trem, basta seguir o tutorial e praticar um pouco.

Contras:
- Infelizmente, o motor do jogo é mal otimizado causando várias quedas de FPS;
- Seria ideal se o sistema DVA fosse acessível também pelo teclado. 

Meu Sistema: 
Windows 7 Professional 64bit
AMD FX 4100 Quad-Core processor 3.60 Ghz
500GB HD
Nvidia Geforce GTX 750
4GB RAM
